# **1. MACRO REGIME DRIVERS FOR TAIWAN**

Taiwan is one of the **purest global-tech-cycle, export-driven economies** in the world. Macro trading begins with **TSMC → Electronics cycle → Exports → FX reserves → CBC (central bank) policy → TWD & Rates.**

## **1.1 The Three Big Macro Regimes**

### **(A) Global Semiconductor Upcycle**

* Rising global tech demand
* Strong shipments (TSMC, ASE, UMC)
* Export orders ↑
* Export value ↑
* Current account ↑
* CBC accumulates reserves
* **TWD tends to appreciate slowly** (but CBC caps volatility)
* Local rates stable
* Equity market rallies (TWSE = beta to tech)

### **(B) Tech Downcycle / Global Inventory Correction**

* Tech shipments fall
* Exports contract
* Current account narrows
* CBC stops appreciation pressure
* **TWD weakens in controlled fashion**
* CBC sometimes lets TWD depreciate gradually to support exports
* TWSE underperforms global tech

### **(C) Geopolitical Risk Regime**

* US–China tensions
* Military tensions
* Taiwan premium widens
* **USD/TWD spikes abruptly**
* Outflows from equities
* CBC intervenes aggressively
* Local bond yields may fall (flight-to-quality)

